{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"229be2e18abe6ecf10887f7bd183a1b76f292452073a7d529552290471744485","slug":"papers.connectomics.index","location":"/papers/connectomics/index.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Connectomics","description":"Connectome mapping, graph-theoretic analysis, C. elegans, Drosophila, and the human connectome project.","content_includes_title":false,"exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"index.md","url":"/index-abd1f119de29c28b5f4addfa1a36b565.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Scope","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"key":"hG9t1WtcC8"}],"identifier":"scope","label":"Scope","html_id":"scope","implicit":true,"key":"mRg7fYpy86"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Connectomics is the systematic reconstruction and analysis of neural wiring diagrams at cellular or subcellular resolution. Using serial electron microscopy, expansion microscopy, or light-sheet fluorescence imaging, researchers reconstruct all neurons and synapses in a tissue volume and represent them as a directed, weighted graph. The resulting connectome is the structural substrate within which all neural computation must occur.","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"kOQETA0YBh"}],"key":"TJfddCwtWk"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Relevance","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"J1isPCIhBU"}],"identifier":"relevance","label":"Relevance","html_id":"relevance","implicit":true,"key":"NPaNX6rvlO"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A circuit’s connectivity matrix constrains which computations it can perform and which dynamical states it can express. Connectomes provide structural ground truth against which network models can be tested, and they reveal organisational principles, small-world topology, rich-club structure, hub nodes, that are increasingly used as design targets for neuromorphic architectures. The complete wiring of small organisms enables whole-organism neural simulation: the 302-neuron C. elegans connectome, complete since 1986, remains the canonical benchmark.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"key":"CChVYV229i"}],"key":"o5MdFaZfNk"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cross-references","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"bVxrhrbPbz"}],"identifier":"cross-references","label":"Cross-references","html_id":"cross-references","implicit":true,"key":"BNz4SB9vDP"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Connectomes provide structural constraints for the network models in ","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"n02NP9Cs2s"},{"type":"link","url":"/papers/network-dynamics","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Network Dynamics","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"s0XyTzrNhI"}],"urlSource":"../network-dynamics/index.md","dataUrl":"/papers.network-dynamics.index.json","internal":true,"protocol":"file","key":"u798NVZVmJ"},{"type":"text","value":" and inform the circuit-level detail in ","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"GZkkv8GVMn"},{"type":"link","url":"/papers/cortex-physiology","positi